V1.0.0
enable identify object through two camera.
Track RGB signals across image rows and columns. 
First, perform an initial separation based on color change: if the color changes dramatically, separate the region into different objects. 
Second, perform another separation based on depth: if the depth change is not smooth, separate the region into different objects. 
Finally, run a CNN to extract visual features from each separated region.
In this stage, calculation time doesn't matter. It's acceptable that the algorthm is too complicated.
V0.0.1 changing the logic. Introduce attention. Use attention to select region to do depth measure and object features extract.
